  "signature": "ed25519:9b2d4f1e7a3c056b8e2f4a1d9c3b7e5f2a0d8c6b4e1f3a7d9c2b5e0f8a3d6c4",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software QA at Gradation 2 requires documented version control, regression testing for primary solver routines, and a traceable build record. Achieved level is confirmed by the ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 validation certificate and internal QA log.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2) is a commercially validated platform with documented version control and regression test suites. Internal QA records confirm that the build used for all Morrison COU1 simulations is traceable to a released version with no open critical defect reports. Gradation 2 is appropriate for MRL 2 at Class II device risk."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 2 requires demonstration that the solver correctly implements the governing equations through at least one benchmark problem with known analytical or manufactured solution. The Taylor–Green vortex and Poiseuille flow benchmarks satisfy this criterion.",
      "rationale": "Code verification was performed using the method of manufactured solutions for the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations and confirmed against the Taylor–Green vortex benchmark. Observed order of accuracy (1.97) is consistent with the second-order spatial discretisation scheme. Results are documented in the solver verification report SVR-2023-04."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the baseline pump geometry at the design operating point (5 L/min, 2500 rpm). The Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the volume-averaged scalar stress was 1.8% between the medium and fine meshes, well below the 5% threshold adopted for this assessment. The fine mesh (14.2 million polyhedral cells) was selected for all production runs. Achieving Gradation 3 provides additional confidence beyond the MRL 2 minimum requirement of Gradation 2. The required level of 2 reflects the minimum mandated by the MRL 2 matrix; the team elected to exceed it given the sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to near-wall shear stress resolution."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 2 requires that experimental test conditions used for validation are documented with sufficient detail to allow replication, including fluid properties, boundary conditions, and measurement uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "Experimental validation data were obtained from the FDA benchmark hemolysis study (Hariharan et al. 2011). Test conditions—including blood analogue fluid viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s), density (1056 kg/m³), inlet flow rates, and rotational speeds—are fully documented in the published protocol. Temperature was controlled to 37 °C ± 0.5 °C throughout testing. All five operating points used in the COU are represented in the experimental dataset."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 2 requires a quantitative comparison metric between model outputs and experimental measurements, with documented agreement bounds. The normalised RMS error threshold of 15% on the relative hemolysis index across all five operating points constitutes the acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RHI) values were compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. The normalised RMS error was 9.3%, within the 15% threshold. Individual operating point comparisons show no systematic bias. Model predictions correctly rank-order the five operating conditions, confirming the model's utility for identifying worst-case hemolysis scenarios."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest (QoI) is the volume-averaged scalar shear stress used as input to the Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model, which directly yields the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH). This QoI is directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device). The Gradation 2 requirement for MRL 2 is met because the QoI is explicitly defined, measurable, and maps unambiguously onto the clinical endpoint. No surrogate or proxy quantities are used in the final decision metric."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 2 requires that validation activities are performed on a geometry and flow regime sufficiently similar to the COU geometry and operating conditions to support extrapolation of credibility conclusions. Similarity is assessed via Reynolds number ratio, geometric fidelity score, and fluid property match.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares the same impeller topology and hydraulic diameter range as the device under evaluation. Operating Reynolds numbers span the same regime (Re 1200–4800). The fluid analogue (aqueous glycerol, 36% v/v) matches the viscosity and density of blood within 4%. Geometric differences between the validation pump and the COU device are within the tolerance band being evaluated, making the validation activities directly relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 is required for numerical solver error, reflecting the expectation that a commercially validated solver is used with default convergence tolerances. ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 residual convergence to 1×10⁻⁵ for all equations was confirmed for every simulation. No iterative divergence or oscillation was observed. The required level of 1 is consistent with the MRL 2 credibility matrix and is met by the documented convergence records."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup was performed by an experienced CFD analyst (5+ years rotary blood pump CFD) and independently reviewed by a second analyst prior to production runs. Boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and solver settings were cross-checked against the documented simulation plan SP-COU1-2023. No use errors were identified during review. Achieving Gradation 2 exceeds the MRL 2 minimum requirement of Gradation 1, providing additional assurance against operator-induced error in a safety-relevant application."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The RANS k-ω SST turbulence model was selected based on its established performance for confined rotating flow with adverse pressure gradients. Model form uncertainty was assessed by comparing k-ω SST predictions against LES results from the literature for a geometrically similar centrifugal pump at matched Re. Volume-averaged scalar stress predictions agreed within 12%. The Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis correlation is the standard model form for this device class and is consistent with FDA guidance on computational hemolysis assessment. Gradation 2 is met through documented model selection rationale and literature-supported performance benchmarking."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 2 requires that all model inputs are identified and their sources documented; uncertainty in primary inputs (viscosity, density, rotational speed) must be characterised qualitatively.",
      "rationale": "Model inputs factor is not assessed at MRL 2 for this COU because the input parameter space is bounded by the manufacturing tolerance study design, and input uncertainty is captured implicitly through the five operating-point sweep. The not-assessed status is acceptable per the MRL 2 credibility matrix for Class II devices where model influence is Medium."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "Test samples factor is not assessed at MRL 2. The FDA benchmark dataset used for validation was obtained from a single pump specimen; sample-to-sample variability was not characterised within the scope of this COU. This is acceptable at MRL 2 for a Class II device with Medium model influence, as documented in the credibility planning record CPR-COU1-2023."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The equivalency of input parameters between the validation case and the COU was evaluated by comparing fluid properties, rotational speed range, and flow rate range. Viscosity ratio (validation/COU): 0.98; density ratio: 1.00; rotational speed overlap: 100%; flow rate overlap: 100%. All five COU operating points fall within the validated operating envelope. The required Gradation 2 level is met because the input parameter space of the COU is fully contained within the validation dataset, supporting direct transfer of credibility conclusions without extrapolation."
    }
  ],
